Head subquadrate in dorsal outline; cranial sutures absent. Vertex with broadly triangulate area of rugosity; eyes proportionally small, slightly protruding, and distinctly subtriangular. Ocelli small, elliptical, nearly touching eye. Antennae with 14–16 articles; formula 2 < 3 > 4 = 5 . Pronotum with weak rugosity along lateral lobes. Anterior and posterior margins of pronotum very shallowly concave; sides nearly parallel. In some specimens, posterior corners of pronotum subtruncate. Markings on pronotum indistinct. Fore wing radius (
Fig. 5
) reaching wing margin about at two-fifths wing length from suture; radial sector with 6–9 anterior branches. Wing membrane between veins covered with tiny round papillae. Small arolia present. Mandible dentition typical of genus (
Fig. 6
).
